'''Rollin Summers Sturgeon''' (August 25, 1877 &ndash; May 10, 1961) was an [[United States|American]] [[film director]] of [[silent film]]s <ref name="SpehrLundquist1996">{{cite book|author1=Paul C. Spehr|author2=Gunnar Lundquist|author3=Einar Lauritzen|title=American film personnel and company credits, 1908-1920: filmographies reordered by authoritative organizational and personal names from Lauritzen and Lundquist's American film-index|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YX1ZAAAAMAAJ|date=1996|publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc.|isbn=978-0-7864-0255-7}}</ref> active from
1910 to 1924. He directed 101 films during this period.

==Filmography==
[[File:Betty and the Buccaneers - Rollin S. Sturgeon - 1917 - Universal - EYE FLM - OB 685673.ogv|thumb|Video of the romantic adventure silent film ''Betty and the buccaneers'' (1917, Rollin S. Sturgeon, 1:05:10 running time). Collection [[EYE Film Institute Netherlands]].]]
[[File:All dolled up - Rollin S. Sturgeon 1921 Universal EYE FLM2206 OB 685751 hires.webm|thumb|Video of the romantic comedy silent film ''All dolled up'' (1921, Rollin S. Sturgeon, 37:38 running time). Collection EYE Film Institute Netherlands.]]

